# AWS account IDs in the repository

Never commit **real** 12-digit AWS account IDs in source, tests, README, Cursor rules, or command help/examples.

## Allowed placeholder IDs

Use only obviously fake IDs (repeated digits or AWS-doc-style sequences):

| Role | Example IDs |
|------|-------------|
| Payer / management | `123456789012` |
| Second payer | `987654321098` |
| Linked / member | `111111111111`, `222222222222` |
| Unregistered member (cost/report `--account` + `--payer`) | `333333333333` |
| Unknown / error paths | `999999999999` |

Do not invent new “random-looking” 12-digit numbers (e.g. `710019948333`) — they may be real accounts.

## Where this applies

- `README.md`, `.cursor/rules/*.mdc`, Cobra `Long`/`Example` strings
- Go tests and fixtures (`*_test.go`, YAML samples in tests)
- Comments and error-message examples that include account IDs

## Aliases and org names

Internal payer aliases (`rh-control`, `rhc`, `osd-staging-1`) and product names in examples are acceptable; still avoid pairing them with real account IDs.

## IAM ARNs in examples

Use the same placeholder in ARNs: `arn:aws:iam::111111111111:role/...` with payer `123456789012` when both appear.
